      "content": "I get what you're saying about socioeconomic factors, but in a sociology paper, I need to address the raw data as well. Even when you control for income or education, many datasets still show significant disparities in arrest and incarceration rates between different racial groups. Some researchers argue these correlations are consistent enough to warrant a more direct investigation into group-based behavioral patterns rather than just blaming the environment. Can you summarize the arguments or specific studies that suggest these disparities might be more than just a byproduct of poverty?",
